---+++ From Wiki (Newspaper)
   * ?Using Argumentation Schemes for Argument Extraction: A Bottom-Up Method (Walton, 2012) IGI Global
      * focuses on Walton's argumentation schemes; tries to cluster schemes by similarity...
      * "It was found that 37.1% of the arguments collected did not fit any of the fourteen schemes" 
   * ? Pushing Toulmin Too Far: Learning From an Argument Representation Scheme (Newman & Marshall, 1992) [[http://www.csdl.tamu.edu/~marshall/toulmin.pdf][Technical report]]<br/>
     This paper (43 pages) is a survey on the key factors that need to be thought of when applying an argumentation scheme.
     It investigates the suitability of Toulmin's scheme and suggests some improvements.
      * p3 Some interesting thoughts on the assumption of independence of content and argumentative structure. Understanding argumentation (incl. used discourse markers) depends largely on a *shared background*.
      * p4 Standard linear format is not optimal for presenting argumentation. (Schum and Martin, 1985)
      * Further Reading:
         * Schum and Martin, 1985) Schum D. and Martin, A, "Formal and Empirical Research on Cascaded Inference in Jurisprudence." Law and Society Review, Vol. 7, No. 1, 1982, pp. 105-152
   * Argument extraction for supporting public policy formulation (Florou et al, 2013) [[http://aclweb.org/anthology/W/W13/W13-2707.pdf][ACL WS 2013]]
      * %X% as a motivator?
   * Active participation within written argumentation: metadiscourse and editorialist&#8217;s authority ([[http://ac.els-cdn.com/S0378216603000328/1-s2.0-S0378216603000328-main.pdf?_tid=e257b13a-3731-11e3-b4b3-00000aab0f6c&acdnat=1382017494_8f507e5bcaf2a22d2d1451ecee6aeb9e][Le 2002]])
   * Appraisal and Journalistic Discourse [[[http://grammatics.com/Appraisal/MediaLit-Comment.pdf][Rick Iedema, Susan Feez and Peter White, 1994]]]
      * rather for thesis than for paper; not very scientific, rather a survey
   * Reported speech as an element of argumentative newspaper discourse [[[http://dcm.sagepub.com/content/3/1/79.short#aff-1][Smirnova, 2009]]] 
   * Who speaks for whom? Towards analyzing opinions in news editorials [[[http://www.irit.fr/~Patrick.Saint-Dizier/publi_fichier/P43.pdf][Bald and Saint-Dizier, 2009]]]
      * most recent work: Bal Krishna Bal, Patrick Saint-Dizier. Towards Building Annotated Resources for Analyzing Opinions and Argumentation in News Editorials, LREC, Malta, Nicoletta Calzolari (Eds.), ELRA, may 2010. 
      * %X% most similar work!



